ie.cit.group3.controller

Class BrowseController

  • java.lang.Object
    • ie.cit.group3.controller.BrowseController

  • @Controller
@RequestMapping(value="/browse")
public class BrowseController
extends java.lang.Object
    Author:
    John Murphy This class handles the URL "/browse" requests. This class interfaces with the dispatchServlet to handles its URL requests and serves it the data (ModelMap) and html file to use to display the data.

      • BrowseOptions

        @RequestMapping(value="/",
                method=GET)
public java.lang.String BrowseOptions(org.springframework.ui.ModelMap model)
        BrowseOptions: This method captures the /browse/ URL. It uses the form backing bean: "GeneralFormBackingBean". It supplies the following data to the html form: blank form backing bean, blank message (this will be populated if no search info is found), count of the number of objects in the database, count of the number of participants in the database and count of the number of roles in the database RequestMethod.GET
        Parameters:
        ModelMap - model
        Returns:
        displayOptions.html as view
